\c 5
\s1 Descendants of Adam
\p
\v 1-2 God created men and women to be like himself. He gave them his blessing and called them human beings. This is a list of the descendants of Adam, the first man:\x - \xo 5.1,2: \xt Gn 1.27,28.\x*\x - \xo 5.2: \xt Mt 19.4; Mk 10.6.\x*
\p
\v 3-4 When Adam was one hundred and thirty, he had a son who was just like him, and he named him Seth. Adam had more children
\v 5 and died at the age of nine hundred and thirty.
\p
\v 6 When Seth was one hundred and five, he had a son named Enosh.
\v 7 Seth had more children
\v 8 and died at the age of nine hundred and twelve.
\p
\v 9 When Enosh was ninety, he had a son named Kenan.
\v 10 Enosh had more children
\v 11 and died at the age of nine hundred and five.
\p
\v 12 When Kenan was seventy, he had a son named Mahalalel.
\v 13 Kenan had more children
\v 14 and died at the age of nine hundred and ten.
\p
\v 15 When Mahalalel was sixty-five, he had a son named Jared.
\v 16 Mahalalel had more children
\v 17 and died at the age of eight hundred and ninety-five.
\p
\v 18 When Jared was one hundred and sixty-two, he had a son named Enoch.
\v 19 Jared had more children
\v 20 and died at the age of nine hundred and sixty-two.
\p
\v 21 When Enoch was sixty-five, he had a son named Methuselah,
\v 22 and during the next three hundred years he had more children. Enoch truly loved God,
\v 23-24 and God took him away at the age of three hundred and sixty-five.\x - \xo 5.24: \xt He 11.5; Jd 14.\x*
\p
\v 25 When Methuselah was one hundred and eighty-seven, he had a son named Lamech.
\v 26 Methuselah had more children
\v 27 and died at the age of nine hundred and sixty-nine.
\p
\v 28 When Lamech was one hundred and eighty-two, he had a son.
\v 29 Lamech said, “I'll name him Noah because he will give us comfort,\f + \fr 5.29 \fq Noah...comfort: \ft In Hebrew “Noah” sounds like “comfort”.\f* as we struggle hard to make a living on this land that the \nd Lord\nd* has put under a curse.”
\v 30 Lamech had more children
\v 31 and died at the age of seven hundred and seventy-seven.
\p
\v 32 After Noah was five hundred years old, he had three sons and named them Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
